HEADWORD: Hammercloth
<hw>Ham"mer*cloth`</hw> <pr>(-kl⟦ocr⟧th; 115)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Prob. fr. D. <ets>hemel</ets> heaven, canopy, tester (akin to G.
<ets>himmel</ets>, and perh. also to E. <ets>heaven</ets>) + E.
<ets>cloth</ets>; or perh. a corruption of <ets>hamper
cloth</ets>.]</ety> <def>The cloth which covers a coach box.</def>⟦br⟧
